    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PUSCH scheduling validation in RA procedure\n\n### Summary\nDuring random access procedure, the gNB scheduler incorrectly handled PUSCH configuration for Msg3 transmission. When the AMF triggered a high load scenario, the scheduler allocated invalid MCS indices (>27) for Msg3 PUSCH, causing corruption in the UL grant field of the RAR message. This led to UE failing to transmit Msg3 and eventually RACH failure.\n\nThe issue was traced to missing validation of PUSCH parameters before constructing the UL grant. Under certain timing conditions between CU and DU, the MCS index could be left uninitialized, causing the UL grant construction to use garbage values.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_RA.c`: Added validation checks in `nr_add_msg3()` to ensure MCS index is within valid range (0-27) and RB allocation does not exceed BWP size before calling `nr_fill_rar()`.\n\nReproduction steps:\n1. Configure gNB with aggressive RACH parameters (prach-ConfigurationIndex: 157, zeroCorrelationZoneConfig: 13)\n2. Trigger 50+ concurrent UEs attempting RA simultaneously\n3. Monitor for \"Invalid MCS index\" assertion failures or RAR decoding errors in UEs\n4. Check gNB logs for segmentation faults during `nr_fill_rar()` execution\n\nThe fix prevents invalid PUSCH parameters from propagating to the RAR construction, ensuring proper Msg3 scheduling even under high load conditions.\n"
}